\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1  \b0 It increases with temperature. It has the formula:\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qc\i VT = kT/q\par
\i0\fs20 (here k is the Boltzmann constant, T is the temperature in kelvin and q is the charge of an electron)\fs24\par

